<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3702] Remove xml-apis.jar because we no longer have to compile against jdk1.3</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3702</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Knut Anders raised the issue of whether we still need this jar file: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Is-xml-apis.jar-still-needed--td17584026.html#a17584026&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Is-xml-apis.jar-still-needed--td17584026.html#a17584026&lt;/a&gt; I have built Derby without this jar file and run the regression tests under Java 5 and jdk1.4: they passed cleanly for me in both environments. I believe we can remove this jar file, which was added in revision 395643 in order to compile the xml support under jdk1.3--we no longer support that platform.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
